      "content": "```markdown\n# NexusStream Endpoint\n\n## Overview\n\nThe NexusStream endpoint provides a scalable and efficient way to stream data between applications. This endpoint is designed to handle large volumes of data and is optimized for real-time communication.\n\n## Request Method\n\nThe NexusStream endpoint accepts POST requests.\n\n## Request URL\n\nThe NexusStream endpoint is located at `/v1/stream`.\n\n## Request Body\n\nThe request body should contain the following parameters:\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Name | Type | Description | Required |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `stream_id` | `string` | The unique identifier for the stream session. | Yes |\n| `buffer_size` | `integer` | Size of the data buffer in KB. | Yes |\n\n### Example Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stream_id\": \"1234567890\",\n  \"buffer_size\": 1024\n}\n```\n\n## Response\n\nThe NexusStream endpoint returns a JSON response with the following structure:\n\n### Response\n\n| Name | Type | Description | Required |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `stream_id` | `string` | The unique identifier for the stream session. | Yes |\n| `buffer_size` | `integer` | Size",
